eces (approx. 3 cm)","1 tbsp pepitas","400 g canned black beans, rinsed and drained (approx. 250 g after draining)","2 tbsp chickpea (besan) flour","1 - 2 tsp ground smoked paprika (optional)","1 tsp liquid smoke seasoning (optional - see Tips)"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["180 g sour cream","2 - 3 tsp horseradish cream","6 slider buns (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r150468","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-QyUJq3Xpsm0\/XZVQlvwrVcI\/AAAAAAAAdDE\/NOL-oAelEeAWhJTdAn_KnrVtYbTXI_2NQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RoOedH6V7wyrseHq.png","title":"Smoky beetroot and black bean sliders with soused cucumber","publishedAt":"2018-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.3 g","fat":"27.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.6 g","calories":"1836 kJ \/ 437 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, small bowl, large non-stick frying pan, large plate, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["You can find liquid smoke at specialty food stores, some supermarkets and online. It adds a delicious smoky flavour to foods (minus the fire!).","We used our <i>Buckwheat and almond slider buns<\/i> (please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip), but you can use any type of roll or bun you like."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}